## 2026-03-28 - Race condition in file write guard
- Replaced fixed 500ms `setTimeout` cleanup of `_writingFiles` entries with event-driven cleanup: the watcher callbacks now clear the guard when they see (and suppress) a write-triggered event. A 30-second fallback timeout prevents memory leaks if the watcher never fires.
- Changed `_writingFiles` from `Set<string>` to `Map<string, ReturnType<typeof setTimeout>>` to track per-file fallback timers.
- Added `_startWriteGuard(filePath)` and `_clearWriteGuard(filePath)` helper methods.

